Here’s the “Phase 2 / later” feature list — everything that’s **not required for MVP**, but would take your app from “works” to “enterprise-grade form platform”.

## Form capabilities

* **Sections / pages** (group fields into steps, progress indicator)
* **Conditional logic**

  * show/hide fields based on other answers
  * conditional required (“required if X is true”)
* **Advanced validation rules**

  * min/max (number + date)
  * minLength/maxLength (text)
  * regex pattern validation
  * “must be one of” / “must include”
* **Repeating groups / tables**

  * “add multiple defects/items” with same sub-fields
* **Computed fields**

  * auto-calculations (qty × rate, scoring, etc.)
* **Field types expansion**

  * textarea, radio, multiselect, file (non-photo), signature
  * location/GPS, barcode/QR scan, time picker
* **Draft submissions (autosave)**

  * save partial form and continue later
* **Offline-first mobile**

  * fill forms offline, sync when online

## Review workflow upgrades

* **Multi-step approvals** (L1 → L2 approval)
* **Assignment rules** (auto-assign to manager by plant/shift)
* **Comments thread** on submissions
* **Re-open / resubmit** flow after rejection

## Analytics & reporting

* **Export submissions** (CSV/Excel/PDF)
* **Scheduled reports** (daily/weekly email)
* **Trends per field** (e.g., defect counts by type)
* **SLA metrics** (time-to-review, pending aging by plant)

## Template lifecycle / governance

* **Template change history** (audit log: who edited/published/archived)
* **Role-based permissions per plant** (fine-grained RBAC)
* **Template approval workflow** (draft needs approval before publish)
* **Deprecation strategy** (sunset old templates gracefully)

## Attachments & files

* **Multiple photos per field**
* **Image compression on mobile**
* **Virus scan / file scanning** (enterprise security)
* **Retention policies** (auto-delete after X days)

## Platform / ops

* **Rate limiting** (protect APIs)
* **Structured logging + tracing** (request IDs)
* **Better error codes** (stable error contract for frontend)
* **Migration scripts** (instead of `synchronize: true`)
* **CI/CD pipelines** for web + backend + mobile builds

That’s your “after everything is done” backlog. The first chunk to tackle later (highest ROI) is usually: **sections/pages + advanced validations + conditional required/show**.
